development training sessions and staff meetings as required    Work with cadets on both group and individual basis to help foster their understanding of the course related subject area material and their own learning abilities and study skills    Arrive for individual tutoring appointments and groups tutoring sessions on time  and keep appointments and sessions on schedule  stay alert  minimize distractions from tutoring    Communicate effectively with cadet athletes by establishing positive rapport and by keeping a professional  patient  and engaged demeanor    Support by the unit s tutoring philosophy  be familiar with the VMI Honor Code  and never do a cadet s work for him or her or render a cadet improper academic aid assistance    Other duties as assigned  Minimum Qualifications    A Bachelor s degree or higher or be a full time student seeking a Bachelor s Degree    Have successfully completed the class es  or a similar class to be tutored as an undergraduate or graduate student and have made a grade of B or better  or have demonstrated through relevant professional experience  nursing  teaching etc  mastery of the material to be tutored  Preferred Qualifications    A Bachelor s Degree or higher in the discipline  or related discipline  to that which they will tutor or be A student seeking a Bachelor s Degree in the discipline to be tutored    Have a 3 0 cumulative GPA or higher as an undergraduate    Have successfully completed the class es  or a similar class to be tutored as an undergraduate or graduate student and have made a grade of B or better  Apply online at  http virginiajobs peopleadmin com postings 11691   Salary   10 00 15 00 hourly depending on qualifications Applications accepted until position is filled  VMI is an Equal Opportunity Employer and does not discriminate against anyone because of race  color  religion  national origin  political affiliation  sex  age  or disability  AmeriCorps  Peace Corps and other national service alumni are also encouraged to apply  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 